body.name: Seville Classics Mega Lockable Storage Cabinet, 48" W x 24" D x 72" H, Granite
body.stockDetail: Only 3 left in stock - order soon.
features: STURDY ALL-STEEL STORAGE - Our storage cabinet is extra-large (4' W) and designed for high-capacity commercial-use in professional environments. Cabinet includes wall straps for additional security when fully loaded.
LOCKING STAINLESS-STEEL DOORS - Secure your things behind stainless-steel doors finished with UltraGuard fingerprint-resistant coating. Lock the doors with the included keys for superior security.

ADJUSTABLE SHELVES - Cabinet includes 3 solid-steel shelves that are adjustable at 1-inch increments. Remove or rearrange shelves as desired to store tall pieces of equipment, appliances, gear, and more!
HEAVY-DUTY STEEL BODY - Store up to 600 lbs evenly distributed throughout the unit. Solid steel panels keep your supplies safe. Ribbed side panels help protect against dents and divots from impact.
EASY ASSEMBLY - Assembly is easy with all required tools and detailed assembly instructions included.
body.description: Optimize your storage with Seville Classics UltraHD® Tall Stainless Steel 2-Door Lockable Storage Cabinet. This unit is designed to optimize large spaces with a footprint of 48" wide by 24" deep. Doors are constructed of high-quality grade 430 stainless steel with recessed handles and key lock. An UltraGuard® fingerprint-resistant coating on the doors help to resist smudges from grease and oil. They're also ferromagnetic, working with magnetic hangers, labels, white boards and other accessories. Easily organize the interior with 3 steel shelves height adjustable at 1-inch increments. Cabinet body is constructed of steel and features a ribbed exterior to protect against dents from impacts at work. Black polyurethane bumpers and grade 430 stainless-steel corner guards provide extra durability when you're on the move or in busy spaces. Cabinet includes padded leveling feet and wall mounting straps for superior stability in almost any space. Assembly is easy with all required tools and detailed assembly instructions included.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks really good in our garage.
reviews.reviewText: Very sturdy. Holds alot of items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 26, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Pros:-I purchased the 30 in.W X 18 in.D X 72 in, MODEL UHD20162B-Very nice cabinet for the garage.-Easy to assemble but it takes hours to assemble. It took me 2.5 hours with a power drill and I am handy and have done this kind of assembly before.-Parts are labeled and screws come in numbered bags which is great.-It is well packed. I expected at least one dented part but all were satisfactory, no dents.-The tools provided are great. The screw driver provided is magnetic which I used to start the screw as to not strip the screw tread with the power drill. The wrench for adjusting the legs also worked satisfactorily. -The cabinet is sturdy and all the parts fit together well. I expected the doors to not line up but the doors aligned well. I thought I would need to drill holes for some unaligned part. No drilling required.-The shelves could be heavier duty but you can always cut a piece of ¾” plywood to put on top of the shelf as the design of corner shelf holders should be able to hold a lot more weight.-Straps are provided to secure to the wall.Cons:-It should have one more shelf.-The “Engineered Nylon Anchors for quick assembly” are just garbage. The manufacturer should have provided all screws. Screws are faster and hold stronger than nylon anchors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality Except for the Doors
reviews.reviewText: Great looking storage cabinet that was reasonably easy to assemble. Some of the materials/pieces are a little flimsy. The doors in particular not solid and because of how they ship the doors come in two pieces which make them less than secure. Love the look and the amount of storage though!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works for us and looks nice
reviews.reviewText: Well it was very easy for me concerning the assembly as my husband did that. He said it was fairly easy. Lets just say he got it together in a day. It cleared a lot of clutter in the garage and looks nice and neat.I am thinking of getting another one but have to be tactful about when to put that on the honey do list. Great product and the price is great as well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was searching for garage storage and this company came up.Thier video on the process making this product sold me on it and I read all the great reviews and thought I would give it a try. Impressed by the packaging, the easy to assemble instructions( all the pieces are labled clearly so that you really can not go wrong assembling). I am so impressed by the quality and sturdiness of this product without breaking the bank! I ordered 5 cabinets and will order more as I continue to organize my garage. The wheels are heavy duty and roll quite easily. It does reccomend building with 2 people, but as a 57 year old lady I built by myself without a problem. It can be done. I would say I spent 2 hours building the first one and it gets quicker as you build more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid cabinet, looks great
reviews.reviewText: Although a bit pricey, this cabinet is built well and looks great. Lots of storage space on the shelves. Definitely nicer than those flimsy plastic storage cabinets where the shelves warp if you put more than 5 pounds on them. Easy to assemble for what it is.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Like instructions say, don't tighten anything up until it's alined and flush.
reviews.reviewText: Awesome cabinet with lots of room, the only thing wrong with the whole ordeal was the shipper did not handle the package (FEDEX) with care which resulted in quite a few dings, dents and bent parts. I was able to straighten everything out enough to assemble. Plans on talking with the manufacturer to see if I can get an extra shelf for my efforts??

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Don’t agree about the sturdiness of this cabinet. I find it quit flimsy, the so called metal to be extremely thin. For the price of this item I was expecting a better grade of metal that would be quite a bit stronger. I’m afraid to put anything relatively heavy in this cabinet especially on the base. With their spot welding and thin materials I have little confidence it will survive.
